This paper deals with wireless communication systems and focuses on the impact of imperfect channel state information on the performance of a downlink max-based scheduling scheme. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). However, the paper also considers delay constraints, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper uses mathematical analysis to derive lower bounds for probability of outage, which could place it in cs.MM (Mathematical Methods) or cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
